    "full_feature_set_caveat": "This full-feature (incl. n_samples) F1=0.941 is NOT trustworthy as a genuine-signal result. feature_importances_ shows n_samples carries 0.969 of total importance -- mean/std/min/max/last are flat (1.0/0.0) across nearly every window because the up{} metric barely moves in a 30s window. The apparent separation is a sample-count-parity artifact between differently-constructed pre_failure vs normal_reference query windows, not broker-health signal (same class of bug as the earlier n_samples window-size leak). See broker_kill_no_nsamples_check.json for the de-confounded result: F1=0.222, p=0.660 (near chance) once n_samples is dropped -- consistent with the baseline detectors recall-limited mechanism (12.5% baseline recall), not a real ML improvement."
